    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2461481">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2461481">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2461481)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2461481">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="2303803"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1456172905 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Feb 2016 20:28</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2461481">
									

<p>I would upvote for the concept and downvote for the writing, I'm afraid, leaving me at a no-vote.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The issues with the writing mostly fall into the &quot;show, don't tell&quot; category, to me; you have a lot of &quot;his name was [name] and he did [action]&quot; going on, whereas I'd recommend throwing that information into dialogue. You have a bunch of characters that rarely speak, and they feel like wasted space when it comes to exposition.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>One by one, they passed through the Gate and onto the other side, the crossing causing conflicting sensations to each member of the task force. Their sight went completely white, while their skin felt as if they had stepped into a hot bath. At the same time, streaks of ice felt as if they were wrapping themselves around their spines.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This part in particular fell flat as I read it. If you're describing overwhelming or elaborate physical sensations, your sentence and paragraph structure should reflect what the characters are feeling, and this doesn't.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>One by one, they passed through the Gate and onto the other side. There were mixed responses from each member of the team as their bodies were overwhelmed with conflicting sensations, their view of the world quickly flashing to a blinding white while their skin burned and prickled as if they'd each been submerged in hot water. (&#8230;)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>(I'm not gonna say that rewrite is perfect by any stretch, but hopefully it illustrates what I'm going for here.)</p>
<p>This goes back to the &quot;show, don't tell&quot; thing, as well as what I said about having characters that never speak; you're telling me that all these people are going to pass through a gateway that makes them feel like they're burning, being frozen from the inside out, and blinded simultaneously and they're not going to say anything about it?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>TL;DR: You have a lot of characters with a lot of potential here and they're not being used to describe the environment and events as much as they should be. Instead they're just given names and jobs and sent on their ways.</p>
<hr />
<p>Edit: The rewrite is great, so upvoted!</p>

