					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=455145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252631" alt="Petrograd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=455145)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;" >Petrograd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1456294968 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Feb 2016 06:22</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2462357">
									

<p>In addition to the show don't tell comments above, your dialogue is incredibly stilted and the topics are extremely cliched. New guy is unimpressed too soon but later wowed (accompanied by ribbing from others)? Complaints about lack of firepower? These are tropes, and you haven't done anything here to elevate them out of that and into character building.</p>
<p>As far as the speech goes, take this from the sergeants first speech:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Please use this time to make sure you have everything you were assigned, for once we pass through the threshold, we’ll be on a one way path until the mission is complete.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't know what kind of tone you intended here, but nobody talks like that. The &quot;for&quot; is really unlikely, and conversationally this would probably be said in shorter sentences. (One old trick is supposed to be to say your dialogue out loud to see if it makes sense.)</p>
<p>There are other pretty generic things that hurt it (e.g., every new character is introduced abruptly by physical description-&gt;name-&gt;first dialogue, so that they all seem plopped into existence when necessary).</p>
<p>Ultimately, -1. I'm definitely interested in the story you want to tell, but the writing quality just falls flat.</p>

							</div>

								
					
